Female (
Fig. 1 B
). Length 6.6 –7.0 mm, width 2.1–2.6 mm , larger, stouter than male; antennae shorter than male, approximately reaching to base of hind angles of pronotum, 4 th antennomere distinctly wider than long ( 1.53–1.57 times); pronotum more convex and 1.05–1.06 times wider than long. Reproductive organs: ovipositor sub-triangular, with styli; vagina (
Fig. 3 B
) elongate; uterus enlarged at anterior, with ballon-like colleterial glands, lacking sclerotised structures; bursa copularix elongate, cylindrical, sub-equal in length with width from base to apical, coiled from apical half, with two accessory glands; basal accessory gland distinctly elongate, longer than second accessory gland.
